      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Facility_Search",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to search for facility records within a billing system based on a provided search text. It retrieves distinct facility details such as the facility sequence ID, OEC facility number, facility name, address, agency name, utility company, city planning BIN, block, lot number, and review status. The search is performed across multiple related tables: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Account",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "UtilityCompany",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Facility",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AgencyDivision",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure uses a common table expression (CTE) to filter and organize the data before returning the results ordered by the facility name."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity is considered medium due to the use of a CTE, multiple table joins, and dynamic search capabilities. The procedure involves data transformation and concatenation, which adds to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@SearchText AS VARCHAR(MAX)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter is used to filter the search results. It allows partial matching against a concatenated string of various facility attributes. If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@SearchText",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "NULL",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", all records are returned without filtering."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
